Wow, a 3.5-year-old thread!

We don&#39;t provide a way to use proxies which require authentication. The 
FetchHTTP.configureProxy() method would be a place to look to start such 
work. However, it doesn&#39;t seem like the HostConfiguration class of the 
HttpClient library that we&#39;re using has an fields/accessors for 
proxy-authentication information, so it might be difficult to add.

If you have sway with the proxy administrators, they might be able to 
allow your crawling machines to use the proxy without an authentication 
challenge (for example, as a whitelisted IP).

- Gordon @ IA

